{"type":"message","id":"e13a3e6d","parentId":"c619bb9d","timestamp":"2026-04-05T08:58:47.740Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the problem clearly. All the `investment-research-background-*` cron tasks (except the preopen one which uses `gmn/gpt-5.4`) are configured with `model: \"minimax-m2.7\"`, but the workspace `USER.md` has a rule that says `default_model: minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7`. However, the error says:\n\n`LiveSessionModelSwitchError: Live session model switch requested: minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7`\n\nThis is the exact same problem mentioned in the memory from yesterday. The cron tasks are configured with `minimax-m2.7` but when they start, the workspace USER.md has `default_model: minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7` which triggers a model switch error.\n \nThe workspace's `USER.md` has a `default_model` directive that conflicts with the model these cron tasks are explicitly configured to use. The real issue is that these isolated sessions shouldn't be inheriting workspace rules at all—they should either get their model from the cron configuration directly or use a separate workspace that doesn't have conflicting model rules. Looking at the memory, we were exploring two solutions to fix this issue - either changing those cron tasks to use `minimax-m2.7` to match the workspace configuration, or isolating them in a separate workspace without the model conflict.\n\nSince the user confirmed yesterday that these were indeed separate Feishu bots (来福来财 vs coding-agent), and the error message shows the model switch is being triggered when the workspace tries to apply its default model, it seems the core problem is that the isolated session configuration isn't properly overriding the workspace-level default.\n\nThe isolated sessions are starting with `minimax-m2.7` as specified in the cron config, but then the workspace `USER.md` is forcing a switch to `MiniMax-M2.7`, causing the conflict. The fix would likely be either removing the `default_model` directive from the workspace files used by these cron jobs, or ensuring the cron task configuration properly bypasses workspace inheritance entirely.","thinkingSignature":"d33f383cc57d2caad07d2122cc7fbb16f12754d556df074229024a044b8d9b87"},{"type":"text","text":"找到问题了。所有来福来财cron任务的错误都是同一个：\n\n> `LiveSessionModelSwitchError: Live session model switch requested: minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7`\n\n**根因：** 这些cron任务配置了`model: minimax-m2.7`，但workspace的`USER.md`里有`default_model: minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7`，启动时模型冲突，直接报错退出。08:40盘前值班之所以正常，是因为它用的是`gmn/gpt-5.4`，不触发这个冲突。\n\n**来福来财cron任务状态一览：**\n| 任务 | 最近成功 | 状态 | 原因 |\n|------|---------|------|------|\n| 08:40 盘前值班 | 04-03 ✅ | 正常 | 用 gpt-5.4，无冲突 |\n| 09:35 数据源健康巡检 | — | ❌ error | 模型冲突 |\n| 09:45 临时会商监控 | — | ❌ error（连续15次）| 模型冲突 |\n| 10:30 盘中值班 | — | ❌ error（连续5次）| 模型冲突 |\n| 16:30 盘后值班 | — | ❌ error（连续4次）| 模型冲突 |\n| 21:00 夜间值班 | — | ❌ error（连续8次）| 模型冲突 |\n\n昨天你说了来福来财和coding-agent是两个不同的bot，这个冲突的源头就是workspace模型规则。需要我修一下吗？方案是把这几个cron的`minimax-m2.7`改成`gmn/gpt-5.4`（和08:40盘前值班一致）。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17585,"output":789,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39841,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775379506993,"responseId":"062157338b9610b5ccc87728452c2d04"}}
